+ * `no-such-tool` means the model addressed a tool that is not in the active
+ * tool set; `invalid-input` means the tool exists but the call's input failed
+ * schema validation (or was not parseable JSON).
+ */
+export type ActionInvalidReason = "invalid-input" | "no-such-tool";
+
+/**
+ * Stream event emitted when the model produces a tool call that fails
+ * validation before execution.
+ *
+ * Invalid calls never execute and never appear in `actions.requested` or
+ * `action.result`; the model still receives the validation error and may
+ * retry. This event makes those pre-execution rejections observable so
+ * consumers can surface or measure them.
